HEADWORD: Smell-less
<hw>Smell"-less</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Destitute of smell; having no
odor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Daisies <qex>smell-less</qex>, yet most quaint.</q> <rj><qau>Beau.
& Fl.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Smelt</ent>⟦br⟧
